The evidence with the title 'Health care in Massachusetts: 'abject failure' or work in progress ... ' says Feb 13, 2012  ... President Obama 's health care overhaul was largely based on one that then-gov. Mitt Romney signed into law in Massachusetts in 2006 . Now, more than 98 percent of state residents have health insurance , and the law has drawn unexpected supporters . But controlling costs remains a challenge. 
